<section class="section vita" id="vita">
  <span class="eyebrow">§ V · Vita</span>

  <div class="bias-grid vita__grid">
    <figure class="vita__figure">
      <img
        src="/images/portrait-romulus-carre.jpg"
        alt="Jack von Wiese und Kaiserswaldau"
        width="1200"
        height="1200"
        loading="lazy"
      />
      <figcaption class="mono">Portrait · ROMULUS</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <div class="vita__text">
      <p>
        I was born in Iowa to a family that has been nobly getting it out of the dirt for over 200 years -
        farmers, engineers, builders. I left at sixteen for the East Coast and then headed west to San
        Francisco - the long-walked path from a small town to a big stage. Childhood was building: LEGO,
        stop-motion, history books, writing, an early conviction that the world could be re-made.
      </p>

      <p>
        At fourteen I started <strong>Back by Popular Demand</strong>, a vintage label run from a bedroom;
        by my sophomore year of high school it had moved 10,000+ pieces and paid for college, zero loans.
      </p>

      <p>
        What followed was a decade in apparel design and manufacturing. <strong>HRMTG</strong> -
        Historical Reinterpretations Made Through Garments, a streetwear label that shipped to twelve
        countries. Brand work for companies as large as $100B and as small as day-zero. Five companies
        before I could legally drink. The through-line was always the same: when my family lost their farm,
        it was because the people who made things did not own the infrastructure they depended on. I have
        been trying to build that infrastructure ever since.
      </p>

      <p>
        That something larger is <strong>ONTHEBIAS</strong>: the AI layer between <em>"I have a design"</em>
        and <em>"a factory can make this."</em> 8.2 billion people get dressed every morning; somewhere
        between the sketch and the seam, the fashion industry runs on duct tape, fax sheets, and faith. I
        intend to replace that with infrastructure.
      </p>

      <p>
        I read Don Quixote in French, Italian, and Spanish - one for the heart, one for the cadence, one
        for the windmills. I speak five languages. I sculpt, I run, I dance, I travel. I keep a copy of
        Marcus Aurelius next to a copy of <em>The Tale of the Bamboo Cutter</em>.
      </p>

      <p class="vita__thesis">
        Everything I make is in service of a single thesis: <strong>that the next century belongs to those
        who can stitch culture, capital, and craft into one cloth - on the bias.</strong>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="vita__triptych" aria-label="Origins">
    <figure class="vita__tri">
      <img src="/images/young-dandy.jpg" alt="Jack as a child, Iowa" width="632" height="805" loading="lazy" />
      <figcaption class="mono">i. <span class="accent">Iowa, c. 2008.</span> Already dressing for the part.</figcaption>
    </figure>
    <figure class="vita__tri">
      <img src="/images/buy-back-farm.jpg" alt="The Wiese family farm in Iowa" width="682" height="881" loading="lazy" />
      <figcaption class="mono">ii. <span class="accent">The farm we lost.</span> 200 years of getting it out of the dirt.</figcaption>
    </figure>
    <figure class="vita__tri">
      <img src="/images/jack-at-magic.jpg" alt="Jack at MAGIC trade show" width="640" height="831" loading="lazy" />
      <figcaption class="mono">iii. <span class="accent">Today.</span> Same kid. Bigger floor.</figcaption>
    </figure>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .vita {
    background: var(--otb-black);
    color: var(--otb-white);
  }
  .vita__grid {
    align-items: start;
    gap: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 5rem);
  }
  .vita__figure {
    margin: 0;
    position: relative;
  }
  .vita__figure img {
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;
    object-fit: cover;
    filter: contrast(1.08) saturate(0.88) brightness(0.96);
  }
  .vita__figure figcaption {
    margin-top: 0.65rem;
    color: var(--otb-mid-gray);
  }
  .vita__text {
    padding-top: 0.25rem;
    color: var(--otb-light-gray);
  }
  .vita__text p {
    font-size: var(--scale-lede);
    line-height: 1.5;
    max-width: 56ch;
  }
  .vita__text strong {
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--otb-white);
  }
  .vita__text em {
    color: var(--otb-white);
  }
  .vita__thesis {
    padding-top: 1rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .vita__thesis strong { color: var(--accent); }

  .vita__triptych {
    margin-top: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 5rem);
    padding-top: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
    gap: clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 2.5rem);
  }
  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .vita__triptych { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
  .vita__tri {
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.6rem;
  }
  .vita__tri img {
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 3 / 4;
    object-fit: cover;
    filter: grayscale(0.2) contrast(1.06) brightness(0.94);
  }
  .vita__tri figcaption {
    color: var(--otb-mid-gray);
    line-height: 1.4;
  }
  .vita__tri figcaption .accent {
    color: var(--accent);
  }
</style>
